<!--
  OWASP Dependency-Check suppression file.

  Use this file to suppress false positives or accepted-risk CVEs so they
  don't fail the CI build. Each suppression should include a comment
  explaining *why* the CVE is suppressed (false positive, not exploitable
  in this context, mitigated by other controls, etc.).

  Docs: https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html

  Example:
  <suppress>
     <notes><![CDATA[ False positive: this CVE applies to the server component, not the client library we use. ]]></notes>
     <cve>CVE-2024-XXXXX</cve>
  </suppress>
-->
